## Errors & mistakes
- Initially proceeded Python-only + clean rename, contradicting the user's AskUserQuestion answers. Corrected.
- zsh: unquoted \$FILES does NOT word-split -> first multi-file sed treated the whole list as one filename (no-op, exit nonzero). Fixed by passing files as literal args. zsh also aliases ls->eza (absent) and grep->ugrep.
- uv run defaulted to Python 3.14t (free-threaded) and tried building grimp (import-linter dep) from Rust -> clang link failure. Fixed: tests via 'uv run --python 3.12 --no-group dev --group test'; lint-imports via '--python 3.12 --group dev'.
- Test bug: asserted weave.TextPart — TextPart is a weave.conversation namespace export, not top-level weave. Fixed to weave.conversation.TextPart.
- Blanket-sed artifacts fixed by hand: "A conversation session."->"A conversation conversation." (->"A conversation."); a "Session SDK" wrapped across two lines in pii_redaction.py docstring; "session-SDK" cross-ref in a claude test comment.

